@Barry Ancona It is true that they needn't. However they do tend to fall under the category of either synonym, definition, factoid, word fragment, or pun, of which this is none. 

It'd be similar to using the simple clue "birch" and the answer being "oak". Yes, they are both tree and wood types, but someone who knows the difference would likely balk at that hint/answer pair.

The fact that both are wetlands is precisely why I suggested "wetland" as an alternate clue (which would fit in the factoid category, a fen is a wetland). Not sure why you felt the need to link the dictionary definitions. The fact that a bog is also a wetland is as irrelevant as pointing out that a birch is also a tree.

